|CKBStreet Samurai Contracts|000

|CK0A contract is Street Samurai membership. An active contract authenticates
the Cortex OS, firmware commands, battle GXP, Edge and Heat, maintenance
automation, the guild strain contribution, clinic coverage, and access to the
private Cortex network.|000

|CKBContract states|000
|CK0Primary means Street Samurai is the character's main guild. Secondary means
another guild is primary while Street Samurai remains active. Both states can
use Street Samurai progression, firmware, hardware, services, and the private
network normally.|000

|CK0Inactive means membership still exists, but equipped gear conflicts with a
guild restriction. Firmware, battle GXP, Edge and Heat activity, maintenance
automation, and the guild strain contribution pause until the conflict is
removed. Installed implants and network membership remain in place.|000

|CKBDiagnosing a paused contract|000
|CK0Samstatus and dashboard identify the contract as inactive. Review recently
equipped armour, weapons, or other restricted gear, remove the conflict, and
check the status again. Inactivity is not caused by low integrity, high
fragmentation, low health, or an unfinished quest.|000

|CKBLeaving|000
|CK0Leaving is different from becoming inactive. It removes membership and
guild systems and permanently destroys installed Street Samurai signature
implants. Unrelated cyberware is unaffected. Read samhelp leaving before
making that decision.|000

|CK0Use samwho to see the primary, secondary, or inactive state of visible
connected operators. Use samhelp hardware for what remains installed and
samhelp maintenance for problems that do not involve contract state.|000
